article info abstract
Apart from biographies and memoirs of outstanding leaders, studies on the development of leaders
in everyday life from childhood to maturity are rare. We propose a developmental model of leaders
in which certain variables formed in early childhood are the basic components for leadership
development in later life. These are a low level of trait anxiety [Spielberger, C.D. (1972). Conceptual
and methodological issues in anxiety research. In C.D. Spielberger (Ed.), Anxiety: Current trends in
theory and research. New York: Academic Press, vol.1] and openness to experiences [Costa, P.T. Jr.,
